                            <h2>Furrow Surfcraft</h3>
                                <p> Furrow Surfcraft is a surfboard shop located in Leucadia, California. Founded by surfer Christine Brailsford Caro.  </p>.

                                <p> The Furrow shaping bay is located inside of the Moonlight-Christenson Glassing factory, where she shapes her boards 100% by hand, using materials all made in California.

                                    Caro graduated from the Laguna College of Art and Design in 2008 with a BFA in illustration.  Aside from shaping, she divides her time between drawing, wood carving, freelance design, surfing, and enjoying time with her family.</p>

                                <figure>
                                    <img src="furrow2.jpg" alt="Christine Brailsford Caro is seen in the shaping bay using a hand shaping tool.">
                                    <figcaption> Caro does all her shaping by hand.</figcaption>
                                </figure>

                                <p> Caro also shaped wooden decks, and numerous wood crafts alongside her surfboard creations. She has received global recognition as a surfboard shaper, with many features in prominent surf magazines worldwide. </p>

                                <figure>
                                    <img src="furrow3.jpg" alt="Christine Brailsford Caro, the owner of Furrow Craft Surf boards, is using a sander to shape a surfboard here.">
                                </figure>
                    
                                <p> Caro creates all kinds of surfboads, on special occasion fulfills special equests, and she iplements fine details in numerous works. She also surfs herselds, and has attempted to teach her dog to surf as well. </p>
